14:17.384 --> 14:27.443
three.

14:36.704 --> 14:43.693
The doctor gave me that medicine and just told me 
all

14:36.704 --> 14:43.693
this. I sure hope you come back again because I'd 
like to hear you sing. The old people used to say,

14:47.097 --> 14:51.082
wonder if I shall ever reach heaven or wonder shall 
I fly. I used to go singing. Well, sometimes I feel

14:54.987 --> 14:59.153
the spirit, you know. I might get to sing someday 
again someday.

15:07.518 --> 15:13.544
Do

15:07.518 --> 15:13.544
you go to church every Sunday, Uncle Finn? Don't go 
to church at all. I listen to the radio. Listen to it

15:18.148 --> 15:20.411
on the radio, huh? Because I tell you why I don't go 
to church.

15:25.916 --> 15:27.618
You'd rather not have this on? You'd rather not 
tell me or you'd rather not have this on when you

15:29.860 --> 15:32.462
tell me? It don't make a difference. I ain't going 
to say nothing wrong. I ain't going to say nothing

15:36.306 --> 15:37.187
wrong. This

15:37.454 --> 15:55.429
is the B-side of AFS recording number 9986, 
